<user_name>Denis Zetino<//user_name><time>1584155028728</time><Rating>4</Rating>< text>
It seems like a popular locale. I was surprised by this place food was good, I was skeptical at first because, of the bad reviews. I thought if I don't see for myself I won't know the reality of it. Their shrimp tacos are very good. The wait to get your food is not out the ordinary, yes ten, or fifteen minutes to get your food out is worth it. The place does get busy, so the busier they are maybe you have to wait a  little longer than that, this place is not a fast-food paced restaurant, I also notice next to Mr clamato there's another small place for tacos, so if you don't like seafood there's another option for you there. Happy eats.</text>

<user>107820699036107109935<//user><Date>1490805889751</Date>< Review>
Before this last visit, I had been to this salon twice before and had really good experiences, so much so that I thought I had found my regular go-to place and was thrilled. On the third visit I had a very different experience. I had a manicure with Susan and I can easily say of the hundreds of manicures I have had in my life this was one of the worst. I asked her to trim my nails a little and she cut them all completely off and then only filed one side on all of them so that there was a sharp edge... on. every. single. nail. I had to go home and file them myself. She then went on to completely hack up my cuticles. As in you can see on my fingers all around the edges where she cut skin and now, 5 days later they are still peeling and red. She painted the polish so thick that after 35 minutes under the heated lamp and fan they were still not dry and I smudged 3 of them while trying to pay. Which brings me onto my next point‚Äî I am not sure how their price scale works, but the previous week I went in for a pedicure and it was $19. This manicure cost $15. I am almost positive I only paid about $10 previously. So I had to sit back down after being there for about an hour already and have her fix the nails. Yes, it was my fault for smudging them, but she did not use quick dry or come over to check and make sure they were dry like the girls always do. Her version of fixing them was taking off the polish, painting two coats of color and that is it. No base coat and no top coat. Like I mentioned, I have had good experiences here in the past, but Susan is by far the worst manicurist I have ever been to. It hasn't even lasted a week. Do not let Susan near your nails!< /Review>

<Date>1556326880449</Date>< Rate>
4< /Rate>
< Text>
4-1/2 stars, only because of difficulty parking and a little more expensive.  You all need to remember that your animal cannot talk to the vet. The veterinarian is not a mind reader. They have diagnostic tools and training - how would human doctors treat patients if the patient could not speak? The same way veterinarians do with their patients. That said, it is a Great veterinary hospital. Plenty of staff to keep you informed. Parking is sometimes difficult because it is so popular. Wide variety of medical services available.  They do not have after hours emergency services but they have very extended open hours.  If you call in advance they can sometimes see you same day.  You pay a little extra for the Urgent Care appointments. My father and grandfather were veterinarians - so I know how to evaluate a good veterinarian and would not recommend if they fell short. Dr. Erin Scott and Dr Vega saved by labs life with with an emergency GDV because his stomach had flipped over.  Thank you very much!</Text>

< Review>
Came in with Penny for a case of constant vomiting, dehydration and lethargy. The team was very nice and helpful and they truly care about the animals. My issue was that their billing practice is highly concerning. I got an estimate originally that ranged between $1500 and $2500 and included a ton of stuff that wasn't clearly necessary. I have been seeing Dr Pogrel (and lately Dr Adam Scott while Dr Pogrel is on sabbatical) for about ten years now. Both vets have lovingly cared for all my pets - Great Dane, Corgi, 3 Ragdoll Cats and my Jack Russell Terrier. Even though I have moved from Livermore to Pleasanton to Walnut Creek, I still make the drive to have my pets taken care of by this amazing staff! The front office staff is always pleasant and helpful (and seem to really enjoy working here!) and both Dr Pogrel & Dr Adam Scott have been consistent in recommending the best course of action for all our pets. I‚Äôve been to many vets that try and up sell products or who recommend expensive (and sometimes unnecessary) treatments, but neither vet has ever done this to us. I trust them wholeheartedly with the health of our pets, and will continue seeing them.

I have mixed feelings on their boarding facility however. <Name>Lera</Name><date>1534222917682</date>< rating>
1</rating>
<Text>I recommended Bishop Ranch in the past, but would like to share what happened to my dog, which will hopefully help others avoid repeating the same mistake.

I took my dog there first because I thought he swallowed something. He stopped eating and was vomiting. After X-rays and an ultrasound and two days on fluids in a hospital he was sent home diagnosed with pancreatitis. Later that week the problem became more severe and we brought him back. The pancreatitis was ruled out. A couple of years ago he had surgery to resect his intestines due to an obstruction, so we were prepared for a similar situation.

I trusted my dog was in good hands with Dr. Vega at Bishop Ranch. He was aware of my dog‚Äôs history, but during an exploratory surgery, he decided to perform a corrective resection as there was scar tissue evident from before. Not only was I unprepared for a major surgery to occur, but was shocked that a specialist wasn‚Äôt given the chance to review his condition beforehand. After the surgery I was informed that my dog was left with very little of his intestinal tract and that the good news was that he had awoken from the anesthesia.

Within 24 hours, it was obvious that there were complications as my dog wasn‚Äôt eating, was shaking, and had a painful tummy. It was only after another 48 hours of suffering for both me and my dog that I had him released from Bishop‚Äôs care and rushed to UC Davis for an urgent visit, as he was obviously in critical condition. What Bishop Ranch either did not have the time or resources to diagnose, was a relatively easy job for the specialists at UC Davis. Within 1 hour we were informed that the surgery had leaked and my dog had become septic with tremendous amounts of inflammation resulting in the pain he was experiencing. The overall prognosis was a 25% chance of recovery with an even lower likelihood of a good quality of life. We had no choice but to euthanize him that night. This was the hardest day of my life. While Bishop Ranch may be fine for most typical veterinary needs, they were completely out of their league in this case. What feels the most unsettling of all is that they didn‚Äôt feel the need to consult a specialist before or after the procedure.

After losing my dog, I sent a message to Dr. Vega telling him what happened since it was his day off, however I haven‚Äôt heard a word back.</Text><pictures>None</pictures>< Resp>

<Rate>1</Rate><review>Let me start by saying that this vet used to be our go to vet for our pets and we would always recommend this place to friends. Dr. Gilman has been our primary doc for yrs and he's been a big help. The staff was always so nice & caring. Over the past couple years, they have become more of a money making establishment than a veterinary clinic. Not only are their services overpriced but some of the treatments & diagnosis are not 100% accurate :( I understand vet visits aren't cheap so I'm not expecting to walk out of there without paying under $60-$70. But at BR it has gotten a little out of control.
I brought my other cat in a few months ago suspecting that he has ear mites because he keeps itching it & shaking his head. The vet (not Dr. Gilman) looks at it and says that it was just wax... He cleans it out and I walk out of there about $245 later, what!?! We get home and over the next few days he seemed to be doing better but as a few months progressed, so did his ear itching. I decide to bring him to another vet (Parkway Vet) with great reviews in Dublin. Dr. Tanner was very sweet & even brought me back to look into the microscope to see the actual mites (so gross) but made me feel very comfortable & confident that he was being treated for the right thing. She cleaned it out and treated both ear. And the cost for that... $122!!
Later I call B. Rippoff to ask if they had any other solutions for our other cat's ear mites to find out if they have any recommendations for treating her without having to bring her in... This cat is very nervous & gets stressed easily and ends up going to the bathroom in her carrier every time which is why I was calling instead of making an appointment. We have literally spent thousands of dollars at this place. The money wouldn't be as much of an issue if they didn't treat their patients & clients this way. <Review>I've had Bishop Ranch for 20 years now and most of it with Dr. Izakawa however have used  just about all them through my many family members.  They are quite simply "The Best of the Best" no matter how severe the medical issue.  I have been with them from vaccinations to heart failure and Dr. Iz is quite proactive when it comes to serious "what is it" pet allergies.   When your pet is suffering & you haven't determined what it is yet -- your not sent out the door with simply anti-histamines which maynot stop their suffering.  I started with a pet rat, a very close pet.  We then had a dog who had developed lots of large cysts. We got a Chinchilla at the same time which Dr. Iz stopped the teeth from growing through the brain. Matty our dog had everything imaginable over the years.
Then 8 months after recovering from a serious operation at UC Davis  Matty dropped to the floor of my Mini Van, all 130lbs, with blood pouring out of his mouth.  I called and told them the emergency and drove strait there.  He was unconscious upon arrival and they were there waiting with a stretcher outside.   I knew he was gone........30 min later they came out and said, Matty can go home in a little bit.  Utterly amazed as they gave me my options.  He had a hole in his heart sac and they drained the fluid.  His age was 8 which is old for that large of a dog.  I was presented with two options, one of which was too serious and impossible recovery  for his age given the operation he had 8 mo earlier so they drained the heart sac each week & Chinese herbs so we could spend a wonderful 3 week vacation of his favorite places to say good bye.  TRUE STORY   ---- How they did all that & located it UNDER 10 MINUTES ILL  NEVER KNOW.  They are not cheap, but they are damn excellent and you never know what will happen next. Now there's Mr. Snickers, our little 30lb Havanese who has to lose 8lbs.  It's possible we are facing something serious, I pray every night he is healthy and lives a long life.  I do know, any other vet would NOT HAVE picked up on those symptoms, for us to be on the look out for. < text>
The dentists there are incredibly kind and very welcoming. The person that first saw me, (Lino I believe?) was really cool. Dr Shalaby didn't try to scold me like most dentists do and made me feel very comfortable. Also you could tell that he really focuses on preventative care, and doesn't try to do fillings if he doesn't need to. I have an appointment for my fillings tomorrow. The technology is quite advanced and they do a very in depth job of going over the x-rays.

The hygienist was really nice and very warm and friendly like the rest. My only complaint is in terms of a cleaning it was probably the worst one I've ever had. It's not that he does anything wrong and he seems very knowledgeable it's just that it's incredibly short (I think it's just scheduled that way, I don't think it has anything to do with the hygienist at all). My last cleaning at another office (the actual procedure) lasted around 45 minutes. She used the pick for 20 minutes, polished, lasered, etc. It was very in depth and my teeth (although sore) felt amazingly clean. They felt so clean for the next few MONTHS it was that good.

This one the actual cleaning procedure lasted maybe 15 minutes at best, and that's only because of the extra fluoride polishing procedure I had to purchase that wasn't covered by my free cleaning. He used the pick on my front bottom teeth for a few minutes then had a little polisher that really didn't feel like it did much for about another 2-3 minutes. That was it. My teeth felt the same as I had walked in, with a little bit of fluoride paste on them. I almost felt like calling up another dentist and scheduling my second free cleaning (covered by my insurance) on the spot.

Like I said the overall experience was good, and better than most dentist's I've been to because of how personable they are. And the price is very reasonable. Just a suggestion is to be more in depth with the cleaning, as a lot of people are in there just for the cleaning so people should get a better experience out of it. I'm happy to go back there for my fillings, and will update the post with my most likely very positive experience.<//text>

<Rate>5</Rate><review>Hands down one of the best creole restaurants in the I.E. I came here for Mardi Gras and had a blast! Made reservations for 630 but was called by the restaurant to push it to 645, nbd since I knew it would be busy. My party was seated right away after we checked in. The ambiance and live music was amazing, it truly felt like I was back in NOLA. Chef Norm and his staff did a fantastic job getting the food out piping hot and in a timely manner. <UserId.>101269259708855695546</UserId.><username>Marc Saunders</username><date>1558928867441</date>< Rate>
5</Rate>
< Review>
Short answer: Good.

Long answer: We ate family style, (I wasn't expecting this) our hostess made arrangements for us to served several courses; Shrimp Grits, 2 salads (tomato basil & a garlic something or another), then a chicken or fish dish, both Cajun style, served over a bed of rice and cheesecake, or sorbet or bread pudding for dessert.

1st off, let me preface this by telling you I'm an EXTREMELY picky eater. I really shy away from textures, colors and squishy, mushy foods which look unappealing to me. To my detriment I know, I miss out on a lot of stuff, but most times, I just cant get past this...but I digress.

I made a point not to eat a lot at a BBQ we went to earlier in the day because I was really looking forward to this restaurant, the wife & I love NOLA and the food. Anyway, being served stuff I didn't order myself turns me off, and last night was no exception. I'm telling you this, because surprisingly, I pushed through and really enjoyed just about everything.

I had small portions, mostly because of my squeamish, unnatural paranoia of tastes, texture and smells, but went back and had a 2nd helping of just about everything. It was delicious!  The other thing, even though I ate pretty small portions, I was full at the end of the meal.

I'm glad I rationed myself because I was able to sample every dish.  The flavors were bold (I can't think of a better description of it), and literally each bite I experienced a separate and exciting flavor.

BOTTOM LINE: Going back.  I wanna order some things an see what else they got!

Sorry for the long winded explanation, but this is probably the 1st place I've been to that I believe you just gotta explain the experience.</Review>

We came here to celebrate my cousins Birthday. There are plenty of options to choose from the menu, however for me since I'm allergic to shrimp and now apparently any type of shellfish I'm limited to a small amount to order from the menu. (I really need to go get an allergy test) Everyone, and I do mean everyone in our party ordered something with shrimp or lobster, or pork. (I'm fine with pork lol, it's my sister that's allergic to pork lol) So I was not able to sample not one dish lol, horrible. Well, I ordered the Hanger Steak. It sat on some garlic sweet potatoes, with ratatouille and a medium steak. This was actually very delicious. I would have preferred less sweet potatoes and more ratatouille and I usually complain about veggies. I was able to rotate my dish around to the whole table so they can try it and they all loved it as well. I couldn't leave without getting dessert so I got a Creole Cheesecake Oliver and a Bread Pudding with Bourbon Sauce for the table to share. The Birthday girl got her own dessert but we still shared with her. Both desserts were delicious but the best one was the cheesecake. Now since I'm getting older and more sensitive, goodness I hate this I ended up with hives by the end of the meal lol. Man that really sucked. But despite that I wouldn't mind coming back, just maybe probably with some medication on hand lol. Oh and service was excellent!!!<//Text>

< Review>
Please avoid booking your appointment with Amanda Wirth. I had made a last minute appointment to get a simple haircut and was pulled by Amanda. She asked me what I was looking to do and I explained that all I needed was a haircut and showed her a picture. She said "okay let me take you to the back to wash your hair", so I followed her. She sat me at a hair washing station and the proceeded to wash my hair...That is when things went sideways. Someone else comes into the room and tell her she needs to clean her station. I had just washed my hair in the morning and let it air dry and by the time I got there it was pretty much dry but very very slightly damp. All I wanted was my hair curled too but instead of asking me the lady pulled out her hair dryer for a "blow out" which only lasted maybe 10minutes before it shorted. She went on to curl my hair. 2 or 3 irons shorted while doing my hair. I came in thinking I would only pay around $25 with tip. Normally the curl would be $21 but because she didn't ask and did a "blow out" it was an extra $18, so instead of $21 it was $39 plus $5 tip. I don't make much money and was blindsided by the outrageous exta price. Halfway through my event the curls were almost completely fallen. I was so unhappy not only for the unexpected extra charge but that my hair didn't even last the night. A terrible experience and not sure I would come again for any salon appointment especially if I'm going to get charged for a service I never asked for. :-(<//Text><Pics>None</Pics><response>None</response><GmapID>0x80dd2e536f430ea9:0xb56fc5d02329aa45< /GmapID></record></dataset><record>

<Review>I visited 5 other gynecologists, who frankly were pretty arrogant and disrespectful, questioning my pain, to find answers about what could be causing me so much pain. The answers I got were: constipation, not getting pregnant, and having period for too many years, or that I need to start taking hormonal treatment. Their ultrasounds found nothing, and the doctors said they would need to perform exploratory surgery to find out what was wrong, but they didn't want to do it, as they did not believe me or said it might be very risky surgery.
As an European, I am used to excellent medical quality service being provided, but I found that I was getting pretty desperate from the lack of answers and help I was receiving from other doctors. Then I came to Dr. Marinescu, who discovered the problem right away. He was very polite and treated me with respect. He was professional and fixed the problem with minimally invasive surgery, and I was home the same day. I only regret that I didn‚Äôt find him sooner, and didn‚Äôt waste my time with those other hack jobs. It would have saved me 2 years of unbearable pain and suffering. Dr. Marinescu cares about his patients, and not about himself or money, as other doctors do. He explains everything and makes sure that patients receive the treatment and care they need. I know that for any future needs for a gynecologist I may have, Dr. Marinescu will be the doctor I visit first and foremost. Honestly he is so nice and amazing, that if I could, I would like him to be also my dentist, general doctor, dermatologist etc. And I can't forget his amazing staff. Such a nice ladies. I never felt so good at doctor's office. Thank you very much Dr. Marinescu for everything!</Review>< gmapID>

< text>
What can I say, number of stars does not possibly dictate the level of competency Dr Marinescu and his staff has shown. My wife went to Dr Marinescu with a level 4 endometriosis exhibiting a frozen pelvis and 3 different ovarian cysts ranging from 16cm, 5cm and 4cm in size that are giving her unbearable pain and fluctuating high temperatures for the past month.

After visiting many other top rated OBGYNs around the OC and greater LA area (some of which are well reviewed and publicized) in hopes of solving her conundrum we are dumbfounded at some of the recommendations given. Plainly put it, while a few believe her condition is too great for them to treat and others are felt like they are just out for money, none had the confidence to acknowledge our main concern for the need to keep her ovary(s) so that we can have a greater chance at having children later. One well publicized doctor didn't even bother to look at her ultrasound and told us after meeting for 5 minutes that he will have to cut her open down the middle due to the size of her cyst which would be impossible to remove via laparoscopy and that she also will likely lose one of her ovary for certain as the largest of the cysts has already enveloped it. While we understand that doctors never give out promises, we would have appreciated more positive attitude and reinforcement which goes a long way of foreshadowing his bedside manner we as patients all look for  and that apparently had been a common negative reflection among other reviewers.

Dr Marinescu on the other hand come well regarded from all the research that we have done and his calm demeanor facing my condition brought comfort and confidence to me that he will be able to do a good job. One 2 hour long laparoscopy and a 2 week recovery later, we are EXTREMELY happy to say that my wife is cyst free and she have BOTH of her ovaries in tact! Not only did Dr Marinescu diagnosed her condition correctly, he also accurately diagnosed the issue dealing with an infection that was causing the fluctuating temperatures related that need to be addressed prior to surgery which would have gave complications if not caught beforehand. His skillful execution with robotic surgery helped remove the large cyst without cutting her wide open, and of course help saved that particular ovary at the same time. His due diligence also made sure the surgery center staff was keeping a watchful eye on her while she stayed overnight at surgery center for post op recovery.

I could not give enough recommendation for Dr Marinescu and his practice. I believe there is no condition too great or complex for him to handle. So if you are suffering from any particularly unique condition and are turmoiling over what to do or how to treat it. Call Dr Marinescu ASAP. And if you gain the level of trust in him as we have, you will not be disappointed in the result. We on the other hand have found our OBGYN for when me and my wife are expecting, and will see Dr Marinescu in the future on a more joyous note!<//text>

(Translated by Google) When I first arrived in the United States, I had a lot of choices for Chinese doctors and foreigners. I also visited several clinics and interviewed several doctors. I heard that some Chinese doctors did not personally witness each time during the inspection. Because there were too many Chinese guests at the time of production, if there were other pregnant women at the same time, it would be impossible for them to give birth in person, but other doctors in the same clinic. Delivery. With a lot of doubts, I finally chose Dr. Marinscu after the comparison of the parties. It turns out that my choice is wise. 1. Personally and meticulously and thoughtful medical attitude: Every time the doctors are examined, Dr. Marinscu carefully checks and answers your questions patiently. 2, caesarean section technology super skilled: nurses during the preparation work I was already nervous, until the doctor came in with a warm smile, telling you about the time course of surgery and appease your nervousness, I calm down. During the operation, my husband and I just talked a few words. The doctor asked the nurse assistants in the delivery room to prepare for the baby. This speed and my husband were dumbfounded. The surprise was so sudden. 3, the team is seriously responsible, especially the Chinese assistant of Dr. Marinscu, in addition to arranging your birth check appointment, communication with the doctor during the birth check-up, is also a 24-hour online customer service, to solve problems for pregnant women in a timely manner, and effectively solve the medical needs of pregnant women. In short, thanks to Dr. Marinscu and his team, I have experienced a safe, secure and comfortable American production journey.

<userid>106925861543047192281< /userid>< review>
So this PetSmart is OK. There prices are pretty high, but every once in a while they have these crazy clearance certificate sales for 75 percent off their already reduced (to normal) red tags. I really like a few of their staff, but I will not longer shop their because of their return policy for when a pet dies within the time to return/refund....which is to bring in the dead animal. I mean I get it maybe for certain things, but it is morbid. I had a (actually 2) fish die, and I had to keep this decaying fish for like a week until I could get back to the store. And fish decay, rot, and stink very quickly. No other pet store I've gotten fish from ask to bring it in. So sick. I'm done with Pet Smart.   Maybe they can add a snapshot app for dead animals or something.</review>

<Rate>2<//Rate><Review>Unfortunately, this store has gone downhill over the past few years.  I only shop here for the aquatic products so I can't speak for their pet grooming and vet services for cats and dogs.  As far as the aquarium products, they have the usual range of popular fish, but most of the fish aren't cared for that well.  There's always dead fish in the sale displays, and they don't have much in variety.  The tanks look uncared for.  The store also decided to block the view of the aquatics with these ugly shelves of dog treats, as if the store didn't already dedicate a majority of the floor space to that!  All the employees fit the same mold, which can't be a coincidence.  Whoever does the hiring only brings on a specific type of worker.  The face-to-face service is friendly enough but you also get the air that no one working there really cares about the store or you at all.  This place had about 2 or 3 really passionate workers but they've long since dissapeared from this location, and no one has filled that vacuum.  I'm not saying everyone has to be passionate about their PetSmart gig, but no one is really interested in the animals that are in their care.  I'd recommend just going to the PetCo down the street on Sepulveda.<//Review>< pictures>
